St Martin
The Foreign, Commonwealth & Development Office (FCDO) advises against all non-essential travel to St Martin, based on the current assessment of COVID-19 risks in the territory.
If you are returning to the UK from St Martin on or after 4am on 3 October, you will need to self-isolate on your return (unless you are exempt). Check the latest guidance for England, Northern Ireland, Scotland and Wales.
St Barthélemy
St Barthélemy remains exempt from the FCDO advice against all non-essential international travel.
